    "_comment_selectiveDisclosure": "The SAR-restricted fields (adverseMedia, sarFilingReference, internalSuspicionFlag) are included in disclosableClaimPaths but intentionally have NO corresponding decodedDisclosures entry — their digests appear only inside the _sd array of the Issuer-JWT and are NEVER appended to any presentation token. This is the cryptographic mechanism that enforces tipping-off protection: the relying party (or data subject) cannot reconstruct the SAR field values even if they receive the SD-JWT VC.",
